=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
אשּׁר   - אשּׁוּר / 'ashshûr  'ashshûr / ash-shoor', ash-shoor'
=== Etymology ===

Apparently from {{HH|833}} (in the sense of successful); 
=== Proper noun ===
Ashshur, the second son of Shem; also his descendants and the country occupied by them (that is, Assyria), its region and its empire: - Asshur, Assur, Assyria, Assyrians. See H838.